Name: kinterval
Version: 0.0.4
Date: 2023-03-03
Author: Sergei I. Zhilin <szhilin@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Sergei I. Zhilin <szhilin@gmail.com>.
Title: Kaucher Interval Arithmetic
Description: Kaucher Interval Arithmetic extends and completes the classical 
 interval arithmetic by adding improper intervals [a,b] a >= b to the set of 
 proper intervals [a,b] a <= b. (Kaucher C., 1980: Interval analysis in the 
 extended interval space // Computing. Supplementum, 2, pp 33-49).

 The source code of kinterval package is based on Octave interval package 
 (by Oliver Heimlich et al.) implementing the classical interval arithmetic. 
 The signatures of kinterval functions are compatible with the ones for 
 Octave interval package when possible. 

 CAUTION. Unlike interval package kinterval does not implement rigorous 
 rounding policy in its early versions.
License: GPLv3+
Depends: Octave (>= 4.4.2)
